text.text: First and foremost, there’s a valet parking you have to pay for! Like you’re a restaurant at that level, absorb the valet, or reach an agreement with them! I thought that’s very uncommon at this level of restaurants. Food is clean and rich in ingredients, but nothing super wow in terms of taste. I didn’t like some dishes actually. I loved the fattoush. No wifi, I had a guest from Singapore, he needed to connect, but there was no wifi! Like come on guys, this is a fancy restaurant! Not sure what it is, but it’s hard to give this place more than 3 for me! The lady serving at our table was super! She tried so hard to be as professional as possible, and I loved her attitude, she’s a 5/5.

displayName.text: AL MAMLAKA Social Dining - المملكة سوشل دايننق

text.text:
The new food hall at Kingdom Centre mall offers a luxurious dining experience with 15 boutique brands and contemporary decor. Ample seating, including outdoor options, and high-quality food make it a great choice. Be prepared for potential wait times on weekends. Worth the price for a food hall experience. I loved the atmosphere in this place.

Highly recommended!

text.text: AL Mamlaka Social Dining is a treasure trove of delightful experiences! The service here is impeccable—attentive, friendly staff who elevate your dining journey. The diverse menu offers a gastronomic adventure; each dish is a fusion of flavors that tantalize the taste buds. The vibrant vibes and ambiance create an inviting atmosphere, perfect for social gatherings. The variety of cuisines and unique offerings ensure there's something for everyone, making it a culinary haven worth savoring.

text.text: The fabulous new food hall at Kingdom Centre. This mall really needs better F&B given the luxury tenant mix and this is a stepping the right direction. This mall needs more than this but 15 boutique brands with lovely contemporary decor is a big help. Lots of seating (including outdoor but it’s beside the parking lot) and quality food. Lineups on the weekend so get there early and be prepared to wait either way to get in or get a table. Not cheap but good quality food as you would expect in a food hall (this is not a food court).

I’ve been coming here since it’s soft opening, I’m a regular guest daily in the early morning. All seems very good, especially the Blended by Lyre’s thanks to Mr. Evan and his team. Also the ovun manakish are good but the problem is their manager who shouts at the staff very loudly. Every other food shop is good. I also don’t like the toilets they don’t mell fresh, and there should be someone to clean more frequently, also it doesn’t seem suitable for such nice dining.
I’d like to thank the person who brought the idea of the social dining to life.

Good Indian restaurant

In Riyadh Center

Parking can be a issue during weekends.

Ambience is exceptional.
Wooden touch.

Whole wheat Rotis are the best. Please do mention whole wheat awhile placing an order. They have variety….👏👏

Cleanliness 👍👍👍
Presentation 👍👍👍👍👍

Reasonable prices.

Upstairs dining area is also ok….but ground floor is more better.

Recommended for Indian taste buds👍👍
